DESIGN PATTERNS - INTRODUCTION

1. What is a Design Pattern ?
- Well established solutions to common software Design Problems
- It's derived from a book called Gang of Four
- It has 23 Design Patterns
- Out of 23, 10 Design Patterns are most frequently occurring

2. Why Design Pattern ?
- It gave developers a shared Vocabulary
- Lets say we have a problem & the other one says use builder. So as soon as he hears the word builder he should understand what has to be done
- Saves lot of time for famous problems, since its provides standard solution
- These are heavily asked in interviews as well

3. Types of Design Pattern

Based on how objects are created, we have 3 categories :

i) Creational Design Pattern
- How will an object be created ?
- How many objects will be created ?

ii) Structural Design Pattern
Before creating objects, we need classes right ?

- How your classes will be structured ?
- What attributes will be there in the class ?
- How will a class interact with other classes ?

iii) Behavioural Design Pattern
- How you will code a particular action ?

4. Deep Dive

i) Creational Design Pattern
    - Singleton
    - Builder
    - Factory (Simple factory, factory method, abstract factory)
    - Prototype
